          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Preserve Our Lakes and Keep Our Environment Safe Act</b></p> <p>This bill directs the Department of Transportation (DOT) to conduct a study to determine the economic and environmental risks of oil or hazardous liquids spills or leaks in the Straits of Mackinac that a failure of onshore, underwater pipeline facilities within the straits would pose to the Great Lakes.</p> <p>In addition, DOT must evaluate the condition and structural integrity of the facilities.</p> <p>DOT shall terminate operations of a facility upon a determination, based on such studies, that risk of hazard to life, property, or the environment warrants termination. </p>]]></text>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
